The All Progressive Congress (APC) has commenced the screening of 38 aspirants for 2023 House of Assembly election in Anambra State. The two-day exercise started on Thursday night at the Marble Arch Hotels, ahead of the primary election Chairman of the screening Committee, Dalhatu Baba-Adama, assured aspirants and other stakeholders of a transparent process in the State. He said the exercise would also be peaceful because all the aspirants for the screening were mature politicians qualified to legislate   Zamfara PDP denies suspension of its Chairman     Yobe Assembly denies impeachment move against Gov. Buni     Igbokwe: I possess requisite skills to make Abia great   He said the exercise was in line with the APC guidelines for aspirants contesting under the party’s platform. Shortly after commencement of the screening, Anambra APC chairman, Chief Basil Ejidike, assured aspirants of free and fair process. Ejidike, said ; “We pray you will do justice to all the aspirants so that by 2023 we will have very good, credible candidates who are going to contest on the platform of our great party and occupy the Anambra State House of Assembly.” He however appealed to Anambra electorate to vote for APC to get more dividends of democracy at the centre.